From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ImmortalWrt
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2026 02:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pmdomain: airoha: add OPP table for CPU PM domain

The airoha-cpufreq driver uses PD_FLAG_REQUIRED_OPP when attaching the
CPU PM domain, which requires the genpd device to have an OPP table
loaded. Without calling dev_pm_opp_of_add_table(), the OPP table
defined in the device tree (operating-points-v2) is never loaded,
causing dev_pm_domain_attach_list() to fail with error 1 and cpufreq
probe to fail.

Add dev_pm_opp_of_add_table() call in the probe function to load the
OPP table from device tree.

Signed-off-by: ImmortalWrt
---
 drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/airoha-cpu-pmdomain.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/airoha-cpu-pmdomain.c
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/airoha-cpu-pmdomain.c
@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@
 #include <linux/arm-smccc.h>
 #include <linux/bitfield.h>
 #include <linux/clk-provider.h>
+#include <linux/pm_opp.h>
 #include <linux/module.h>
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
 #include <linux/pm_domain.h>
@@ -93,6 +94,11 @@ static int airoha_cpu_pmdomain_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;

+	/* Load OPP table from device tree for PD_FLAG_REQUIRED_OPP */
+	ret = devm_pm_opp_of_add_table(dev);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
 	/* Init and register a PD for CPU */
 	pd = &priv->pd;
 	pd->name = "cpu_pd";
